                <h1>Understanding the German Flag: History and Symbolism</h1>
                <p>The German flag features three horizontal stripes: black at the top, red in the middle, and yellow at the bottom. Adopted in 1949, it symbolizes unity, freedom, and democracy. The colors reflect Germany's history and heritage, making it a significant emblem of national pride and identity that resonates with Germans worldwide.</p>
